                            <Heading/>
                            <Paragraph>The Defense Security Cooperation Agency
                                                (DSCA) was established in 1971 and is under the
                                                authority, direction, and control of the Under
                                                Secretary of Defense (Policy). DSCA provides
                                                traditional security assistance functions such as
                                                military assistance, international military
                                                education and training, and foreign military sales.
                                                DSCA also has program management responsibilities
                                                for humanitarian assistance, demining, and other DOD
                                                programs.</Paragraph>
                        </Detail>
